contentrichtext.text: {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox settlement |official_name = Ocumare del Tuy |nickname = |motto = |image_skyline = |image_caption = |image_flag = |image_seal = | pushpin_map = Venezuela |coordinates_display = title |coordinates_region = VE-M |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] |subdivision_type1 = [[States of Venezuela|State]] |subdivision_type2 = [[Municipalities of Venezuela|Municipality]] |subdivision_name = {{flagicon|Venezuela}}[[Venezuela]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Miranda (state)|Miranda]] |subdivision_name2 = [[Lander, Venezuela|Lander Municipality]] |established_title = |established_date = |established_title2 = |established_date2 = |government_type = |leader_title = |leader_name = |area_total_km2 = |population_as_of = 2005 |population_footnotes = |population_total = 166,112 |population_density_km2 = |timezone = [[Venezuelan Standard Time Zone|VST]] |utc_offset = |timezone_DST = |utc_offset_DST = |latd = 10 |latm = 06 |lats = 49 |latNS = N |longd = 66 |longm = 46 |longs = 53 |longEW = W |elevation_footnotes= |elevation_m = 150 |population_blank1_title = [[Demonym]] |population_blank1 = Ocumareño/a |area_code = |postal_code_type = Postal code |postal_code = 1209 |website = |footnotes = }} '''Ocumare del Tuy''' is a city located in [[Miranda State]] in northern [[Venezuela]], the [[shire town]] of the [[Lander, Venezuela|Lander Municipality]]. Ocumare del Tuy is noted for warm and clear weather, with year-round sunshine and 60 days of rainfall annually, and an average temperature that ranges from 64 to 83 °F (18 to 28 °C), but with relatively low humidity. Ocumare del Tuy has a population of around 160,000 (2005), mainly dedicated to agriculture ([[Cocoa bean|cocoa]], [[coffee]], [[sugar cane]]) and livestock farming ([[pig]]s, but also [[cattle]]), with leafy forest and meadows. Ocumare del Tuy was the capital of the state of Miranda between 1904 and 1928, when it moved to [[Petare]] and later to [[Los Teques]]. [[Miami Marlins]] manager [[Ozzie Guillén]] was born here on 20 January 1964. {{DEFAULTSORT:Ocumare Del Tuy}} [[Category:Populated places in Miranda (state)]]
